# Defense Preparation

## Timeline
T-8w: Draft slides + share with advisor
T-4w: Practice with lab group
T-1w: Final polish + check AV setup
T-0: Arrive 30min early, water bottle, backup USB

## Slide Structure (~40 main slides + 5-10 backup)
Cover → Outline → Motivation (2-3) → RQ (1) → Background (3-4) → Related Work (2-3) → Methodology (8-10) → Results (6-8) → Discussion (2-3) → Conclusion (2) → Future Work (1-2) → Q&A

## Common Committee Questions
- "Why X over Y?" → justify from research-design
- "Does assumption hold?" → robustness experiment
- "What is your key insight?" → 1 crisp sentence (memorize)
- "What next?" → 2-3 concrete directions

## Handling Unknown Questions
"I don't know, but here's how I'd think about it: [reasoning]"

## Opening (memorize)
"My thesis investigates [RQ in plain language]. Today I'll show what I found and why it matters."
